5000|$|Saudization or Saudisation of the workforce—the {{replacement}} of foreign workers with Saudi nationals {{in the private}} sector—is the official national policy of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. [...] While many <b>Saudis</b> <b>are</b> employed by the government, {{there are not enough}} jobs for the growing number of youth. As of 2006 the private sector was largely dominated by expatriate workers from Southeast Asia and the Arab world.|$|E
